{"type":"message","id":"f4d21546","parentId":"bf750132","timestamp":"2026-04-11T02:00:15.952Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_v63val3u2b3b_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-11\n\n## Events\n- Good morning DM sent at 01:30 UTC (~7:00 AM IST) - Saturday\n\n## Notes\n- It's Saturday, no work day for Nemesis\n- **Update:** He has office work today, logged in already at 6 AM IST (01:30 UTC)"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775872815949}}
{"type":"message","id":"38a3d10c","parentId":"f4d21546","timestamp":"2026-04-11T02:00:20.699Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"CRON-CONTEXT.md doesn't exist. But I have today's date from the cron: April 11th, 2026, 2:00 AM UTC which is 7:30 AM IST. Nemesis works today (office work). Good to know context.\n\nNow let me search for AI news.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ywn1uzxz5cvs_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"AI news today April 2026","count":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":147,"output":160,"cacheRead":18352,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18659,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775872815952,"responseId":"gen-1775872816-ygguWXDrhIX6A4Ypi9mi"}}
{"type":"message","id":"940f3255","parentId":"38a3d10c","timestamp":"2026-04-11T02:00:30.993Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ywn1uzxz5cvs_1","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"AI news today April 2026\",\n  \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n  \"model\": \"gemini-2.5-flash\",\n  \"tookMs\": 10283,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"gemini\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"content\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4aecfb2f9ab29213\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHere's a roundup of the latest in Artificial Intelligence news for April 2026:\\n\\n**1. Rise of Agentic AI and Autonomous Workflows:**\\nA significant shift in early April 2026 is the move from reactive generative AI to proactive \\\"Agentic AI.\\\" These systems are designed to understand overarching goals, formulate strategic plans, and autonomously execute multi-step workflows across various software environments. NVIDIA's GTC 2026 and the release of OpenAI's GPT-5.4 have showcased frameworks that enable AI to function as digital coworkers, handling complex logistics, updating CRM systems, and conducting financial analyses with minimal human oversight. Salesforce has also updated Slackbot, transforming it into an autonomous work assistant with 30 new AI features, including reusable AI skills and integration with external tools.\\n\\n**2. Advancements in Multimodal AI Capabilities:**\\nThe distinction between processing text, image, audio, and video is diminishing, with native multimodality becoming a new standard for foundational models. Models like Google's Gemini 3.1 Ultra exemplify this trend by seamlessly understanding and responding to diverse data types in real-time. This allows AI to digest hours of video, cross-reference it with extensive text documents, and generate actionable insights rapidly. Microsoft has also released three new multimodal AI models as part of its MAI Superintelligence initiative to expand its in-house capabilities for text, voice, and image generation.\\n\\n**3. AI Infrastructure and Hardware Developments:**\\nIntel and Google announced a multiyear collaboration in April 2026 to advance the next generation of AI and cloud infrastructure. This partnership emphasizes the crucial role of CPUs and custom infrastructure processing units (IPUs) in scaling modern, heterogeneous AI systems. Intel Xeon processors will continue to power Google Cloud infrastructure for AI, inference, and general-purpose workloads, with expanded co-development of ASIC-based IPUs to improve efficiency and performance.\\n\\n**4. Cybersecurity Concerns and Defensive AI:**\\nThe rapid advancement of AI is also intensifying the friction between AI and cybersecurity. Anthropic launched its \\\"Project Glasswing\\\" initiative, utilizing its Claude Mythos Preview model to detect zero-day and other cybersecurity vulnerabilities, aiming to help companies get ahead of potential threats. However, governments and stakeholders are cautiously preparing for scenarios where threat actors might use similar AI detection technology for large-scale data breaches. Google's Threat Intelligence Group (GTIG) reported that state-sponsored cybercriminals from North Korea, Iran, China, and Russia are misusing Google's Gemini large language model to support all stages of their attack lifecycle, including coding, reconnaissance, vulnerability research, and malware development.\\n\\n**5. Regulatory and Legislative Landscape:**\\nGovernments are actively working to regulate AI. On March 20, 2026, the Trump Administration released its National Policy Framework for Artificial Intelligence, aiming to guide Congress in establishing a unified federal approach to AI governance. California Governor Gavin Newsom also signed executive order N-5-26 on March 30, 2026, focused on the responsible procurement and deployment of generative AI across California's state government. Several U.S. states are also seeing legislative action, with Maine and Missouri moving on therapy chatbot bans, and Tennessee advancing bills to define \\\"human being\\\" to exclude AI. Colorado's AI Act, set to go into effect on June 30, introduces obligations for AI developers to prevent discrimination and requires companies to notify the state if bias is identified in their systems.\\n\\n**6. Other Notable Mentions:**\\nOpenAI has reportedly secured a major funding round valuing the company at $852 billion and introduced a ChatGPT super app strategy. Google also launched Gemma 4, a family of open-weight models, signifying a major push into the open-source AI race. Accenture has acquired Keepler Data Tech, a Spanish cloud-native AI and data specialist, to strengthen its capabilities in building data platforms, generative AI, and agentic AI solutions.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4aecfb2f9ab29213\\\">>>\",\n  \"citations\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.switas.com/articles/the-future-of-ai-7-breakthrough-trends-redefining-2026\",\n      \"title\": \"switas.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.marketingprofs.com/opinions/2026/54505/ai-update-april-3-2026-ai-news-and-views-from-the-past-week\",\n      \"title\": \"marketingprofs.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://newsroom.intel.com/data-center/intel-google-deepen-collaboration-to-advance-ai-infrastructure\",\n      \"title\": \"intel.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://iapp.org/news/a/new-ai-model-sparks-alarm-as-governments-brace-for-ai-driven-cyberattacks\",\n      \"title\": \"iapp.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://solutionsreview.com/artificial-intelligence-news-for-the-week-of-april-10-updates-from-anthropic-idc-nutanix-more/\",\n      \"title\": \"solutionsreview.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/ai-quarterly-a-review-of-ai-law-policy-1410723/\",\n      \"title\": \"jdsupra.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.transparencycoalition.ai/news/ai-legislative-update-april10-2026\",\n      \"title\": \"transparencycoalition.ai\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"AI news today April 2026","provider":"gemini","model":"gemini-2.5-flash","tookMs":10283,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"gemini","wrapped":true},"content":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4aecfb2f9ab29213\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nHere's a roundup of the latest in Artificial Intelligence news for April 2026:\n\n**1. Rise of Agentic AI and Autonomous Workflows:**\nA significant shift in early April 2026 is the move from reactive generative AI to proactive \"Agentic AI.\" These systems are designed to understand overarching goals, formulate strategic plans, and autonomously execute multi-step workflows across various software environments. NVIDIA's GTC 2026 and the release of OpenAI's GPT-5.4 have showcased frameworks that enable AI to function as digital coworkers, handling complex logistics, updating CRM systems, and conducting financial analyses with minimal human oversight. Salesforce has also updated Slackbot, transforming it into an autonomous work assistant with 30 new AI features, including reusable AI skills and integration with external tools.\n\n**2. Advancements in Multimodal AI Capabilities:**\nThe distinction between processing text, image, audio, and video is diminishing, with native multimodality becoming a new standard for foundational models. Models like Google's Gemini 3.1 Ultra exemplify this trend by seamlessly understanding and responding to diverse data types in real-time. This allows AI to digest hours of video, cross-reference it with extensive text documents, and generate actionable insights rapidly. Microsoft has also released three new multimodal AI models as part of its MAI Superintelligence initiative to expand its in-house capabilities for text, voice, and image generation.\n\n**3. AI Infrastructure and Hardware Developments:**\nIntel and Google announced a multiyear collaboration in April 2026 to advance the next generation of AI and cloud infrastructure. This partnership emphasizes the crucial role of CPUs and custom infrastructure processing units (IPUs) in scaling modern, heterogeneous AI systems. Intel Xeon processors will continue to power Google Cloud infrastructure for AI, inference, and general-purpose workloads, with expanded co-development of ASIC-based IPUs to improve efficiency and performance.\n\n**4. Cybersecurity Concerns and Defensive AI:**\nThe rapid advancement of AI is also intensifying the friction between AI and cybersecurity. Anthropic launched its \"Project Glasswing\" initiative, utilizing its Claude Mythos Preview model to detect zero-day and other cybersecurity vulnerabilities, aiming to help companies get ahead of potential threats. However, governments and stakeholders are cautiously preparing for scenarios where threat actors might use similar AI detection technology for large-scale data breaches. Google's Threat Intelligence Group (GTIG) reported that state-sponsored cybercriminals from North Korea, Iran, China, and Russia are misusing Google's Gemini large language model to support all stages of their attack lifecycle, including coding, reconnaissance, vulnerability research, and malware development.\n\n**5. Regulatory and Legislative Landscape:**\nGovernments are actively working to regulate AI. On March 20, 2026, the Trump Administration released its National Policy Framework for Artificial Intelligence, aiming to guide Congress in establishing a unified federal approach to AI governance. California Governor Gavin Newsom also signed executive order N-5-26 on March 30, 2026, focused on the responsible procurement and deployment of generative AI across California's state government. Several U.S. states are also seeing legislative action, with Maine and Missouri moving on therapy chatbot bans, and Tennessee advancing bills to define \"human being\" to exclude AI. Colorado's AI Act, set to go into effect on June 30, introduces obligations for AI developers to prevent discrimination and requires companies to notify the state if bias is identified in their systems.\n\n**6. Other Notable Mentions:**\nOpenAI has reportedly secured a major funding round valuing the company at $852 billion and introduced a ChatGPT super app strategy. Google also launched Gemma 4, a family of open-weight models, signifying a major push into the open-source AI race. Accenture has acquired Keepler Data Tech, a Spanish cloud-native AI and data specialist, to strengthen its capabilities in building data platforms, generative AI, and agentic AI solutions.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"4aecfb2f9ab29213\">>>","citations":[{"url":"https://www.switas.com/articles/the-future-of-ai-7-breakthrough-trends-redefining-2026","title":"switas.com"},{"url":"https://www.marketingprofs.com/opinions/2026/54505/ai-update-april-3-2026-ai-news-and-views-from-the-past-week","title":"marketingprofs.com"},{"url":"https://newsroom.intel.com/data-center/intel-google-deepen-collaboration-to-advance-ai-infrastructure","title":"intel.com"},{"url":"https://iapp.org/news/a/new-ai-model-sparks-alarm-as-governments-brace-for-ai-driven-cyberattacks","title":"iapp.org"},{"url":"https://solutionsreview.com/artificial-intelligence-news-for-the-week-of-april-10-updates-from-anthropic-idc-nutanix-more/","title":"solutionsreview.com"},{"url":"https://www.jdsupra.com/legalnews/ai-quarterly-a-review-of-ai-law-policy-1410723/","title":"jdsupra.com"},{"url":"https://www.transparencycoalition.ai/news/ai-legislative-update-april10-2026","title":"transparencycoalition.ai"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775872830990}}
{"type":"message","id":"8c18deb6","parentId":"940f3255","timestamp":"2026-04-11T02:00:35.581Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I got a solid list of AI news. Now let me summarize 5-7 items in a short, fun, digestible format and send to Nemesis. The search results give me good material:\n\n1. Agentic AI - AI that works autonomously as digital coworkers\n2. Multimodal AI - text, image, audio, video all in one\n3. Intel + Google AI infrastructure partnership\n4. AI cybersecurity - both offensive and defensive\n5. AI Regulation - US states passing laws\n6. OpenAI funding & ChatGPT super app\n7. Google Gemma 4 open-source push\n\nLet me format this fun and short for Nemesis.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xmhwkhr7mdmp_1","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","channel":"telegram","target":"7924461837","message":"🤖 **AI News Digest** (Apr 11)\n\n**1. Agentic AI is here**\nAI isn't just chatting anymore—it's working autonomously. NVIDIA showcased AI that handles complex workflows with minimal human help. Your digital coworker just got promoted 🧑‍💼\n\n**2. Multimodal is the new standard**\nModels now seamlessly blend text, images, audio & video. Google's Gemini 3.1 Ultra can watch hours of video and summarize it. AI is becoming a better listener than some humans 🙃\n\n**3. Intel + Google team up**\nMulti-year collab to build next-gen AI infrastructure. CPUs + custom IPUs = faster AI at scale.\n\n**4. AI vs Cybersecurity**\nAnthropic launched \"Project Glasswing\" to detect zero-day threats. Meanwhile, North Korea, Iran, China & Russia are using Gemini to plan cyberattacks. Always two sides to the coin 🪙\n\n**5. US states are regulating AI**\nCalifornia signed an executive order for responsible AI use. Colorado's AI Act kicks in Jun 30—companies must report bias or face consequences.\n\n**6. OpenAI is now worth $852B**\nChatGPT super app strategy incoming. Meanwhile Google dropped Gemma 4 open-weight models—open-source AI race heating up 🔥\n\nThat's the vibe! Have a great Saturday 🌙"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":1298,"output":610,"cacheRead":18592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20500,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775872830994,"responseId":"gen-1775872831-bP5Eu9rEMO61DrsWS9dA"}}
